            <fr:parent>hodge-theory-ii-1.3</fr:parent>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Dually, <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.1.3" href="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.1.3.xml" taxon="Equation" number="1.3.1.3" /> identifies <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_r^{pq}]]></fr:tex> with a sub-object of a quotient of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K^{p+q}]]></fr:tex>, whence a new filtration <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F_{d^*}]]></fr:tex> induced by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>, called the <fr:em>second direct filtration</fr:em>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
